Sure, here are some examples of sentences in Serbian that use the word "srela" in different forms and positions:

1. *Srela* sam te sinoć na ulici. (I met you last night on the street.)
2. Sinoć sam *srela* tebe na ulici. (Last night I met you on the street.)
3. Kada si me *srela* prvi put? (When did you meet me for the first time?)
4. Nisam te *srela* od prošlog leta. (I haven't seen you since last summer.)
5. *Srela* sam tvoju sestru u prodavnici. (I met your sister in the store.)
6. Čini mi se da sam te *srela* negde pre. (It seems to me that I met you somewhere before.)

In all of these examples, "srela" is used in the past tense of the verb "sresti" (to meet). The word "srela" is highlighted with an asterisk (*) for clarity. The English translations are provided in parentheses after each sentence.